: 86<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 2:42:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> I need a validity check on this one...This could be bug exploitation, but I was told at one time when I was in Sol A (only been there twice), there is a certain keyboard keystrokes you should perform if you should fall into lava.  From what I remember it is something like ALT+F4.  I believe the logic was this sends a disconnect command to the server which immediately disconnects you (unlike a Link Dead state).  So when you log back on, your position will be approx 6 seconds (or the last server update) before you disconnected, effectively where you were before entering the lava.  Is this true.  I recently restarted and was speculating going to Sol A to hunt.  Thanks. <br>
<br>
Besides being burnt to a crisp if one does fall into the lava, what are some of the best methods to get yourself out.  No flames please (pun intended).<br>
<br>
Czak<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mithlin>Mithlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 2:53:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> First get a rogue to help.  And get them a lev spell.  Most likely you will fall into the lava right at the entrance.  I am not sure if there is a way out in Sol A or not.  But if you run around in a panic long enough you will end up in Sol B.  If you die in Sol A the rogue will need to drag your corpse out from that side if possible or at least somewhere near a path where it can be summoned simply.  If it is in Sol B, the rogue will need to zone and drag it through the king room out to the entrance to Lavastorm.  The key is the levitate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twotribes>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 637<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 3:00:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> One solution.....<br>
<br>
Get levitate, and you need to know where the body is. Get as close to the body as you can without going in the lava. Once over the spot where the body is in the lava slowly step out from the ledge a little at a time using summon corpse(/corpse). Eventually you will summon the corpse and still be able to return to the ledge as you havent completely left it. Drag the corpse to a safe spot.<br>
<br>
This works in the entryway area, I know I have done it with my corpse long ago.<br>
<br>
If your not sure where exactly in the lava you are use a bard or necro or sk and locate corpse till your over the spot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shabbashadowsong>Shabba Shadowsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 3:54:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> Get all the fire resist gear you can, get some buffs, then get a bard to play his FR song with a nice drum.  At 200 or so FR I think I was taking like 6 dmg per tick swimming around in it.  This would be easily offset with a high lvl regen spell.  Corpse could easily be pulled before you tick off 2000hp.<br>
<br>
 <p>Shabba Shadowsong<br>
58 Troubador<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=481547">My Magelo Profile</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.wolvesofantonica.co.uk/">Wolves of Antonica</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mithlin>Mithlin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 144<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 4:47:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> There should never be any need to swim around.  Levitate will take you anywhere you need to go without getting hurt.  As a rogue, give me levitate and I can get any corpse out of Sol A and out of some places in Sol B without getting hurt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rosfuil>rosfuil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 4:57:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.rainweaver.com/EQ/Rose/Images/Sketches/Rose-Small-Sq.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> Without having to repeat the tale of that fateful day, I can say that Mithlin has a great deal of experience dealing with lava, dying in lava, and retrieving things from lava.<br>
<br>
I'd take his advice as being pretty solid <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
~Rose <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=smallcutepuppy>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 663<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 5:09:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> Alt-F4 is a windows shortcut to close the currently running program. If it even works from within EQ, all I think it would do is cause the EQ program to crash. So I think it'd be the same as going LD any of the &quot;normal&quot; ways. Sometimes I accidentally hit alt-tab and it kicks me back to desktop (only on my old machine though; my &quot;good&quot; system seems to ignore it), and if I'm dualboxing I'll see that character go LD and hang for the usual 30 seconds before poofing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=beolron>Beolron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 5:44:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/levanoff2/Photos/tepes1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> My experiance with Sol A lava has developed a technique for the entrance pools.<br>
<br>
If I fall in, I swim at the wall, back towards where the pendulum is, and on the side that you enter from.  There is a spot here that on can climb the wall just enough to keep from burning to death while a call for help is sent out.  The damage doesn't stop, but is reduced to a bearable level for one with say 60 FR. Don't stop swimming / climbing though, or the damage will resume as normal.<br>
<br>
Two ways out at that point,  levitate, which can be tricky as you need the right spot to climb the walls per se.  Method two is have a wizard or druid port or x-locate you out of there.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/levanoff2/Photos/sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;">The only certain thing in life, is death. The Old Father planned that event for each of us long ago.<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> All we can do is meet it on our own terms, match it blow for blow, and die honorably.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nehlurra>Nehlurra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 6:42:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~cynnamin/eq/avalurra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> ALT + F4 is a windows key sequence that immediately shuts down the active program or window.<br>
<br>
If you ALT + F4, depending on your version of Windows, in say, Internet Explorer, either the active IE window closes OR all of them close.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure if it's any different than a link death, though... because it just terminates Everquest totally and that can be construed as a Link Death... it just crashes the program, basically.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't do this if I was anyone, I'd find someone to help me get my stuff back... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noggy25>Noggy25</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/16/02 11:12:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> or you could just get a lev ring from me and let me summon you out with CoH.<br>
