Noggy Majaire<br>
56th Mage<br>
Leader of Eternal Redemption <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tasminkittyhawk>tasmin kittyhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/02 8:54:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> What I do, if I do not have aggro is to /quit out of the game as soon as I fall in. You become an NPC which cannot be killed by immersion in lava.<br>
<br>
When you log back in you should be at the zone entrance.<br>
<br>
If you DO have aggro, the mobs will kill you anyway.<br>
<br>
This always used to work for me when I was of a level to hunt in SolA<br>
