<br>
My very first time in there I was going in with a dwarven cleric to help get the ring for the cleric epic.  Well, being a good cleric of brell, she gave me a full stack of Brell's.  Which I promptly drank before going in.  Well we went in and were attacked by the green goblins at the entrance.  It started to run quickly, and I chased it.  It died.  Then I fell into the lava.<br>
<br>
Now drunk out of my mind I start swimming around in a panic.  I get to what seems like loading so I assume I die, but I find I am still in lava, and die a few seconds later.<br>
<br>
So I'm convinced I died in Sol A and run back there looking for where I died.  I look at the /loc I had and found it off the map.  I try summoning and get told I have no corpses in this zone.<br>
<br>
Finally I checked my logs and found before I died I had zoned into Sol B.  So the cleric and I start fighting our way through Sol A to an entrance to Sol B.  However we build up quite a train and I die.  Death #2, and my only rezzed death of the whole thing.<br>
<br>
Finally in Sol B, I started sneaking around, trying to find where it could be.  I ran into a guild group and they knew about where I would be and helped me fight my way there.  We got to a big room with lavafalls and a big pool of lava.  I figured it must be in the pool and jump in to take a look.  There is death #3.<br>
<br>
It is getting late and everyone has to leave.  So I start trying to figure out what I can do.  Finally I get the bright idea to get lev.  So I go out to lavastorm and find a druid who gives me lev.  I then go back into Sol A, walk over the lava flow, zone into Sol B and there is my corpse.  So I drag it out to on a ledge just past the lava fall and start looting.  However I have a few items on me and drop my bow when I loot it.  So I move to try and pick it up, and am attacked.  So I grab my corpse and run as far as I can, almost making it out before I die.  Death #4.<br>
<br>
When a friend died in the lava a few weeks later, I had them out in a matter of minutes after I got there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thewthunderstrike>ThewThunderstrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/02 4:30:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3316.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Escape from Lava</span><hr size=1> <br>
Its been over a year, but last time I fell in lava there, I didnt die because I found a spot in the corner of where 2 walls meet where I could jump out of the lava (at the entrance of sol A).  I was still stuck, and the only way I could stay suspended above the lava was with &quot;auto run&quot; on.  <br>
<br>
(I think I was also able to heal myself while running against the wall, since my loc was not changing.)<br>
<br>
